<br>
Head to the east wall of the zone, across the river.  Move up to the north, near the castle.  Prepare yourself for aggro kiting.  Also be sure to cast lev on yourselves so you don't have to swim if you get too near the river <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Have the wizard invis and run through the castle and up to the wastelands while the mage waits on the east wall.  Head over to the edge of the cliff to the east and find a crystalline golem.  Snare it and hop over the cliff, back to where the mage is waiting on the wall.<br>
<br>
From there, aggro kite the mob up and down the edges of the river.  Down the east wall, across the river, and up the west bank.  It takes a few minutes to kill each mob, but it's very safe.<br>
<br>
At 100% aa, every kill was giving BOTH of us 1 full blue of aa <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A> at: 11/29/02 6:41:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yamp>Yamp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#333333>(12/11/02 4:43:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage wizard duo (or other snaring class) in PoP</span><hr size=1> One great way to duo with a wizard is let the wizard constantly click his/her Flux Staff whenever he/she isn't nuking.  That really helps build up aggro as long as the wizard doesn't run too far. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168753"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.pacbell.net/ping000/Rasc-sig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 8:26:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage wizard duo (or other snaring class) in PoP</span><hr size=1> We don't usually have any problem with aggro.  Even if the mob turns on my pet and kills it, I can summon another while the wizard continues running ahead and nuking.<br>
<br>
It's a very nice combo, and I don't have to sit lfg in PoS, which I absolutely despise doing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=negaburn>negaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 8:24:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  ..</span><hr size=1> the golems arent as easy to snare as they use to be, had 5 snares resisted in a row = gate time.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 8:53:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ..</span><hr size=1> My partner and I are still doing this.  Maybe you had some bad luck.<br>
